,"assoc_campus":null,"assoc_url":"/undergraduate/courses/2021/SAED4051","assoc_class":"Course","assoc_award_titles":null,"assoc_state":"inactive","assoc_award_single":"","assoc_code":"SAED4051","assoc_class_translated_subjects":"Course","assoc_faculty":"Faculty of Arts, Design and Architecture","assoc_class_translated":"Program","assoc_duration_hb_display":"","assoc_current_version":{},"links":[]}],"exclusion":[],"search_title":"ADAD3114 - Research Foundations in Art and Design","description":"<p>Practitioners in the creative industries increasingly articulate the value of their practice in relation to research frameworks. This course explores skills in research methodologies and theories relevant to Art &amp; Design students and provides a suitable foundation for independent investigations and professional practice. The course will introduce you to art and design research methodologies and practice, as well as facilitate the creation of your research direction. You will begin to understand the utility and limits of relevant research frameworks and develop your own approach to them. The aim is to build your confidence in planning, undertaking and evaluating research approaches in order to complete further research oriented study and practice in the future.</p><br />","hb_assessments":[{"delivery_variation":{"cl_id":"d03e343fdbf51c50eb6b147a3a9619c2","name":"Blended in-person / online - Standard (usually weekly or fortnightly)"},"assessments":[{"individual":{"label":null,"value":null},"assessment_name":"Research Project Essay","assessment_type":{"label":"Essay","value":"essay"},"assessment_id":"1","weighting":"30","description":"<p>Essay supporting the development and presentation of the two project works, whether fully realised or propositional in nature, which in themselves respond to research methodologies explored through introduction to UNSW Art &amp; Design research laboratories/research clusters and lectures/tutorials. The essays should take the form of a research proposal, discussing the project work as part of a research schema, and indicating the direction of the future development of the work; the essay is intended as either practice for, or an first draft of, a proposal such as would be used in Honours. The research methodologies explored through the project work are also explained through the accompanying presentation.</p><br />Not specified","learning_outcomes":[{"value":"CLO1","cl_id":"5c3e343fdbf51c50eb6b147a3a9619b8","key":"code"},{"value":"CLO3","cl_id":"d43e343fdbf51c50eb6b147a3a9619be","key":"code"}],"delivery_variations":[],"applies_to_all_delivery_variations":"true","cl_id":"043e343fdbf51c50eb6b147a3a9619a6","links":[]},{"individual":{"label":null,"value":null},"assessment_name":"Research Project Outcome","assessment_type":{"label":"Project","value":"project"},"assessment_id":"2","weighting":"50","description":"<p>Creation of two art/design works, whether fully realised or propositional in nature, which respond to research methodologies explored through introduction to UNSW Art &amp; Design research laboratories/research clusters and lectures/tutorials. The research methodologies explored through the project are also explained in the accompanying essay and presentation.</p>

